tive terminal citrulline-to-arginine route (7 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_004, mol_006, mol_008, mol_009, mol_014\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"<id of best pathway>\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"<overall assessment>\",\n    \"approved\": <true if any pathway approved>,\n    \"hub_quality\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"convergence_quality\": <0.0-1.0>\n}\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.74,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.18,\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.3\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.46,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.58,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.76,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.42,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.5,\n      \"feedback\": \"The path is topologically valid and shows hydrothermal to biochemical flow, but the main weakness is the ornithine-forming step. Pyruvate to alanine is plausible, yet conversion of glyoxylate/pyruvate/alanine directly into an ornithine pool is highly underspecified and chemically weak. Final guanidination of ornithine to arginine is conceptually reasonable only if an activated guanidino donor exists, but free guanidine is a poor d